From: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>
Date: 2026-05-14
Subject: [PATCH] ps4-bpcie: v133 — Orbis chip-tuning write at BAR2+0x10a030

Ghidra decompile of Orbis FW 12.02 bpcie attach function reveals a
previously unreplicated read-modify-write at parent BAR2 + 0x10a030:

  val = (val & 0xfffffe07) | 0xd8     // clear bits 8:3, set bits 3,4,6,7

Region 0x10a000 sits between HPET (0x109000) and UART (0x10e000) in
parent BAR2 — never mapped/programmed in our driver.  Hypothesis: this
tunes a clocking / fabric routing parameter that the TX DMA path
depends on, gating host->chip reads while leaving chip->host RX writes
unaffected.  Strongest remaining hypothesis after v82..v132 exhausted
every BAR0-level avenue.
---
 drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie.c
+++ b/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie.c
@@ -787,6 +787,18 @@
 		ioread32(sc->bar4 + BPCIE_REG_CHIPID_1),
 		ioread32(sc->bar4 + BPCIE_REG_CHIPREV));
 
+	/* v133: Orbis chip-tuning write at parent BAR2 + 0x10a030.
+	 * See FUN_ffffffffc8765090 in Orbis FW 12.02.  Read-modify-write:
+	 * clear bits 8:3, set bits 3,4,6,7 (=0xd8).  Region 0x10a000 sits
+	 * between HPET (0x109000) and UART (0x10e000) in parent BAR2. */
+	{
+		u32 v_before = ioread32(sc->bar2 + 0x10a030);
+		u32 v_after  = (v_before & 0xfffffe07u) | 0xd8u;
+		iowrite32(v_after, sc->bar2 + 0x10a030);
+		sc_info("v133: BAR2+0x10a030 0x%08x -> 0x%08x (Orbis chip tuning)\n",
+			v_before, v_after);
+	}
+
 	//sc->irqdomain = bpcie_create_irq_domain(sc);
 	bpcie_create_irq_domains(sc);
 	if (!sc->irqdomain) {
